# Screen-Level Migration Patterns

## App Screen Structure

```tsx
// ✅ NativeWind Screen Pattern
export default function Screen() {
  const colorScheme = useColorScheme();
  
  return (
    <View className={clsx('flex-1 bg-background', colorScheme === 'dark' && 'dark')}>
      <SafeAreaView className="flex-1">
        {/* Screen content with className styling */}
      </SafeAreaView>
    </View>
  );
}
```

## Navigation Integration

- Ensure navigation components work with NativeWind classes
- Update tab bar styling to use className
- Migrate header configurations to NativeWind approach

## Tab Screens (`(tabs)/`)

- Migrate tab icons to use Tailwind color classes
- Update tab bar background styling
- Ensure consistent theming across tabs

## Dark Mode Implementation

- Use `useColorScheme` hook for theme detection
- Apply `dark` class at screen level
- Ensure all components support dark mode variants

## Import Guidelines

```tsx
// ✅ Correct imports for screens
import { View, Text, SafeAreaView } from 'react-native';
import { useColorScheme } from '@/hooks/useColorScheme';
import { clsx } from 'clsx';

// ❌ Avoid Tamagui imports
// import { Stack, Text } from 'tamagui';
```
